<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-147-258  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 147 258.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics Weekly  Feb 7 1990 n1494 p2(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ferranti SA links cause controversy. (South Africa)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bennett, Chris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A member of Parliament has called for an inquiry into allegedlinks between defense electronics contractor Ferranti PLC andSouth Africa.andP;  Specifically, the concern is over how a formermanager with the South African state arms maker and buyer was soeasily able to become a Ferranti International board member,particularly when the individual had been involved with two mencharged with breaking the embargo on arms-related sales to SoutnAfrica.andP;  A spokesman for Ferranti said the events had taken placelong before the man became a member of Ferranti's board and thatFerranti had no ties to South Africa.andP;  In an unrelatedannouncement, it has been indicated by Ferranti that buy-outoffers have been received on two of its subsidiary companies basedin Dundee, Scotland.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ferranti International Signal PLC (investigations).andO;Topic:     Social IssuesSubsidiary CompaniesEnglandGreat Britain. ParliamentSouth AfricaInvestigations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>